    "12 See Kate Klonick, The New Governors: The People, Rules, and Processes Governing Online Speech, 131 HARV.",
    "1598, 1600-02 (2018) (describing how private platforms \"are now essential to participation in democratic culture\" and regulate online speech in ways that resemble government censorship).",
    "13 See NICOLAS P. SUZOR, LAWLESS: THE SECRET RULES THAT GOVERN OUR DIGITAL LIVES 112-114 (2019) (arguing for the application of \"digital constitutionalism\" to private digital platforms by \"developing new guiding principles that can be applied to the unique way the internet is governed\" and by increasing accountability to overcome public mistrust).",
    "14 See generally Michèle Finck, Digital Co-Regulation: Designing a Supranational Legal",
    "The argument proceeds in three parts: In Part II, I discuss the concept of AI legitimacy and identify two inherent deficits standing in the way of its realization."
